{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation"},{"title":"How-to Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest"],"anchor":"How-to-Guides","generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Wire ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" plugin so the store sees real-time entitlement updates from RevenueCat.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoimplementservice"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"article","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This guide takes you from a wired Swidux app with a paywall slice to a live RevenueCat-backed entitlement pipeline. It covers SDK configuration, plugin registration, observation lifecycle, and refresh\/restore flows.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the API-level reference of the service, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". For the entitlement mapping rules, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". For the upstream plugin contract — actions, state shape, dispatch semantics — see Swidux’s "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a Paywall","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiduxPaywall Reference","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"; this guide does not repeat that material."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Before-you-start","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Before you start"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This guide assumes:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You have a wired Swidux app — ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppState","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"AppAction","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"AppReducer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"AppStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" exist, and the store is in the SwiftUI environment."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppState"},{"text":" already has a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"paywall: PaywallState"},{"text":" slice and your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppAction"},{"text":" has a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".paywall(PaywallAction)"},{"text":" case. If not, follow Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a Paywall"}]},{"text":" guide first.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You have a RevenueCat project, an API key, and at least one entitlement identifier configured in the RevenueCat dashboard."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-1-Add-the-dependencies","level":2,"text":"Step 1: Add the dependencies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add both Swift packages to your ","type":"text"},{"code":"Package.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/HeirloomLogic\/Swidux\", branch: \"main\"),","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/HeirloomLogic\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\", branch: \"main\"),","],"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the products you need to your app target:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":[".target(","    name: \"MyApp\",","    dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"Swidux\", package: \"Swidux\"),","        .product(name: \"SwiduxPaywall\", package: \"Swidux\"),","        .product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),","        .product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),","    ]",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" is optional — drop it if you don’t need the bundled sheets."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-2-Configure-the-paywall-at-launch","level":2,"text":"Step 2: Configure the paywall at launch"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" calls into "},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" under the hood. Configure the paywall before constructing the store:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ MyApp.swift","import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    @State private var store: AppStore","","    init() {","        RevenueCatPaywall.configure(apiKey: \"your_revenuecat_api_key\")","        _store = State(wrappedValue: AppStore.configured())","    }","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup { ContentView().environment(store) }","    }","}"]},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":" traps if used unconfigured. Call "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/RevenueCatPaywall\/configure(apiKey:appUserID:userDefaults:logLevel:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" before anything that constructs "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":", including SwiftUI previews — guard preview-only code with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-3-Construct-the-service","level":2,"text":"Step 3: Construct the service"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create the service with the entitlement identifier you set up in the RevenueCat dashboard:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","","let service = RevenueCatPaywallService(entitlementID: \"pro\")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app sells a separate lifetime SKU alongside a subscription, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for the dual-entitlement form.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-4-Register-the-paywall-plugin","level":2,"text":"Step 4: Register the paywall plugin"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pass the service to ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallPlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when wiring the store:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ AppStore.swift","import Swidux","import SwiduxPaywall","import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","","extension Store where State == AppState, Action == AppAction {","    static func configured() -> AppStore {","        let plugins = PluginHost<AppState, AppAction>()","","        plugins.register(","            PaywallPlugin<AppState, AppAction>(","                state: \\.paywall,","                action: AppAction.paywall,","                extractAction: { if case .paywall(let a) = $0 { return a }; return nil },","                service: RevenueCatPaywallService(entitlementID: \"pro\")","            )","        )","","        return Store(","            initialState: AppState(),","            reducer: AppReducer().reduce,","            plugins: plugins","        )","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The plugin owns reducing for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".paywall"},{"type":"text","text":" actions; your root reducer should fall through with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"return nil"},{"type":"text","text":" for that case."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 5: Observe customer info on launch","anchor":"Step-5-Observe-customer-info-on-launch"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Start the entitlement stream once, on the root view:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ContentView: View {","    @Environment(AppStore.self) private var store","","    var body: some View {","        RootContent()","            .task { store.send(.paywall(.observeCustomerInfo)) }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observeCustomerInfo"},{"text":" returns a long-lived effect that consumes ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService.customerInfoStream()"},{"text":". Every snapshot the service yields flows through ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".customerInfoUpdated"},{"text":" and updates ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.isPro"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasPermanentLicense"},{"text":". The effect lives for the duration of the stream, so the store stays in sync with RevenueCat without polling.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 6: Gate features","anchor":"Step-6-Gate-features"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Read ","type":"text"},{"code":"store.paywall.isGateSatisfied","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" before running gated work. If it’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", dispatch ","type":"text"},{"code":".request(reason:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Button(\"Export PDF\") {","    if store.paywall.isGateSatisfied {","        store.send(.export(.exportPDF))","    } else {","        store.send(.paywall(.request(reason: \"export-pdf\")))","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"isGateSatisfied","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" returns "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when the user holds an active pro subscription "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"or"}]},{"type":"text","text":" a permanent license — feature code does not need to know which."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Step 7: Wire the UI","anchor":"Step-7-Wire-the-UI","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To present "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" and the customer center, attach the bundled sheets to a root view. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Step 8: Restore purchases","anchor":"Step-8-Restore-purchases","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a restore button to your paywall UI. Reflect "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.isLoading"},{"type":"text","text":" to disable it while the call is in flight:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Button(\"Restore Purchases\") {","    store.send(.paywall(.restorePurchases))","}",".disabled(store.paywall.isLoading)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The plugin calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService.restorePurchases()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which forwards to ","type":"text"},{"code":"Purchases.shared.restorePurchases()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". On success the resulting snapshot flows through ","type":"text"},{"code":".customerInfoUpdated","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and updates the gate. On failure, ","type":"text"},{"code":"store.paywall.error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is set.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Step 9: Handle errors","anchor":"Step-9-Handle-errors","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The service throws whatever "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":" throws — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ErrorCode.networkError"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".offlineConnectionError"},{"type":"text","text":", configuration errors, etc. The plugin catches the error and dispatches "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".refreshFailed(message)"},{"type":"text","text":". Read "},{"code":"store.paywall.error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" from your paywall view to surface a retry affordance:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["if let error = store.paywall.error {","    Text(error)","        .foregroundStyle(.red)","    Button(\"Retry\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.refreshCustomerInfo))","    }","}"],"syntax":"swif